I’m just thinking of Highschool Jake & McCall dreaming of one day being married, living at the beach they used to vacation to, in a home they decorated so colourfully together, with a puppy that brings them so much joy, starting Christmas traditions for their future family and now, today, that is our life!!! ❤️My love for you, Jake, grows more and more each day, you bring out the happiest, funniest, most spontaneous and authentic version of me there is and I’ve loved every minute with you since the very beginning!! Thank you for making our 2nd Christmas married such a memorable one! I love you and our little Gilbert family- now let’s go play some football on the beach 😋🫶🏼🌲

Oh what a year it’s been 🫶🏼 TYJ for this beautiful life of ours & that we get to spend it together❤️

Jake, you’re my home. I can’t thank God enough for this life, His creation, and the love He brought to me- I love you my Jake❤️ Excited for a new year, we are ready 2023!! #happynewyear #2022 #2023

To the one who has the ability to turn an ordinary moment into a magical dream 🥹 Our love is my favorite !!! I’m reminded every day of why I choose you Jake Tyler Gilbert- the most caring, selfless, and genuinely kind hearted person I know. I love how you love, it reminds me a whole lot of the way Jesus loves me. You always show up for me. The moment I begin to wonder where you are, I look around only to find you already looking at me. I am so blessed to be the girl who gets to experience your love. It’s the kind of love where you ask me to dance at the most random times, where we lay on the beach and stare at the stars, jump around in the sand and laugh until our stomachs hurt, drive around singing love songs to each other and tearing up. Where we have the most fun simply just being in each other’s arms. It sounds silly but you really are the coolest person I know. I love the way you always look at the bigger picture, the way your mind works, how free spirited and hilarious you are. You truly want the best for everyone and anyone who knows you can see all of this 🫶🏼 You are sincere and passionate in our relationship, I don’t remember the last time I touched a car door, or any door, you ask me to dance whenever I’m feeling low and you strive to always better yourself and our family. You turn to Jesus first in every situation, you pray for me without hesitation or question. You are one in a million and I will never be able to wrap my head around this love that we have. I love our child like love and I love loving you big❤️ Happy 8th Valentine’s Day 🫶🏼

This is your sign to wake up with the sun and start a Bible study with your friends🫶🏼 just a little reminder that a Bible study can look so many different ways, whether it’s on the beach or in your bed, with 5 friends or just by yourself- God doesn’t care what your circumstances look like, He just wants a relationship with you! God doesn’t care about the aesthetic, He created you and simply wants to be with His children. It’s so fun to make Bible studies extra and cute, but the important part is starting where you are & living with a heart like His. Remember the connection is between God and you and He meets you where you’re at ❤️

7 years ago today, Jake left me a note in my mailbox, asked me to meet him in a gazebo, got me Chick-fil-A breakfast before Highschool, a white rose & a red rose and read me the letter where he asked me to be his girlfriend,🥹❤️ For those of you who don’t really know my Jake, let me tell you a little about him🧡 Jake is a man who fears the Lord, he has known right from wrong since way before he knew me, even at age 18 he met every single quality on my “future husband” list of standards and yet he says I’M HIS one of a kind?!❤️ He is humble, so humble he probably doesn’t even want this caption out there😅 He prays for me without question, when I’m sick he prays for me in the name of Jesus again and again until I feel better. He does the little things like always blesses our food whether it’s just us, on a double date or even with a big crowd, he makes sure everyone in the room feels welcomed and seen. He speaks every single week in our Christian community group here and leads so well, he is not ashamed to know Jesus and make Him known. Jake is kind to others, he gives to who ever needs it and truly has the sweetest heart. He lives everyday to appreciate it and that’s a treasure. He is also for sure the smartest person I know 😋 and works hard for what he wants. He passed his real estate test the first time taking it and just got a job as an official real estate agent here in 30A 🥹 Like what😍 I am so proud of him. At the same time he’s a protector, he will fight for me and defend me no matter who it is, and he always checks on me to make sure of how I’m feeling. Jake cares about my best friends and my family as much as I do and that’s something that makes my heart so happy! God sure had a surprise in Jake when he blessed me with him. I sure am proud to be a Gilbert simply because of you🫶🏼 If you’ve read the whole paragraph, that’s just a few of the things I love about him. Anyone who has met Jake has gotten to know all of this 🥹thank you, my love, for asking me to be your girlfriend 7 years ago ❤️I LOVE YOU & the life God has given us together😘

Wow, seems like yesterday we were just 17 year old kids in Highschool with simply a dream of being married to each other to now being married for almost 2 years and living in an answered prayer🥹 From moving away from family for our first year of marriage for Jake’s job to live in out west in Vegas, to taking a leap of faith and moving to the beach we used to vacation to, to pursue our dream jobs and work from home, God has guided us every step of the way for His bigger plan and now led us to our very first home. Living in an answered prayer and I am never going to forget it 🫶🏼 2 years of being married to the love of my life and wow, we have accomplished so many dreams just within these 2 years. We’ve lived in 2 different states and have made some of the best memories ever!! We had our honeymoon in a treehouse, sold our VW vans after renovating them together, we’ve camped in our rooftop tent in about 6 different states, we’ve gotten to dance under the northern lights in Alaska, do handstands on the salt flats, we’ve seen cactuses taller than our house, snowboarded many different peaks across the country, seen the most fiery desert sunsets, snorkeled Catalina island, drove old cars around old Vegas and bought our very first home at the beach we used to vacation to… just to come to the realization we are happiest in each others arms wherever we are 🫶🏼 Jake Gilbert you are my home in every way. I’m reminded every day of why I choose you, you are the most caring, selfless, and genuinely kind hearted person I know. Your love reminds me a whole lot of the way Jesus loves me. You always show up for me. The moment I begin to wonder where you are, I look around only to find you already looking at me. I am so blessed to be girl who gets to experience your love. It’s the kind of love where you ask me to dance at the most random times in random places, where we bring our goggles on every adventure just in case ;) where we jump around in the sand and laugh until our stomachs hurt, where we drive around singing love songs to each other and tearing up. We have the most fun simply just being in each other’s arms. You have the ability to turn an ordinary moment into a perfect new memory❤️ You always start my baths for me, you never let me touch a door, you pray for me without question as many times as it takes, you prioritize me and take me on so many dates, you understand my love language and make sure I always know what you love about me with a note under my pillow❤️ Happy 2 years of marriage my love, I can’t wait for what God has in store for us this year!! These are some of my favorite memories in pictures… Now let’s go camping on the beach and make more memories 🫶🏼⛺️🌊😍

Our birth story (shortened version) 
At 12:30 am on the 31st of December we went in for my scheduled induction. I was 39 weeks and 6 days at this point, it was the day before my due date. We listened to some One Direction on the way to the hospital because One Direction makes me so happy 😂 once we got there and got checked in I got the first pill of Cytotec to get things started but not even 30 minutes later my body went into labor, having contractions every 30 seconds. The nurses didn’t need to continue any induction medicine since my body was doing what it needed to but they were shocked at how many contractions I was having. I went from 3am to 8am having contractions and by then I was ready for the epidural. It wasn’t painful one bit and I’m so glad I got it. I was already 5cm dilated by 9 am and by 12 in the afternoon I was 10cm dilated. Something I didn’t know is that just because you’re 10cm it doesn’t necessarily mean it’s time to push, your baby will get so low that your body will naturally feel like pushing when it’s ready. During that waiting period we had worship music going, we read the Bible, Jake wrote me the sweetest letter ever and we had such a special moment, we also got to watch the 49ers game! 3:00pm came around and it was time to practice pushing since I couldn’t feel anything 😂 and at 4:17pm on 12/31/23 our beautiful boy, Miles, came into the world weighing 8lbs 13oz. Jake and I couldn’t even put it into words we are so in love and so in shock. It truly is a surreal feeling, the most amazing miracle. The birth was so peaceful and beautiful and God was definitely in the room 🩵 the night ended with new years fireworks that we could see from our window. We are so thankful the Father chose us to be his parents🫶🏼

Growing up I always knew I wanted to be a mom🩵 whenever someone would ask me what I wanted to be when I grew up I would always answer with “a wife and a mom.” The moment I held Miles in my arms for the very first time, I felt more love than I even thought was possible, a love I can’t even find the words to describe. In that first breath of his life he became my whole world and that desire in my heart was finally filled ❤️ it truly is my greatest joy to be this little boys mama🥹 Thank you Jesus!!!
